The Bandit Clearance Post was built to provide armed oversight of the canyon approaches after early caravan masters complained that Ashfang Remnant activity was cutting into convoy schedules.  The fieldstone walls are thicker than strictly necessary — a tell of a building designed to withstand siege rather than merely shelter a patrol — and the interior shutters on the western window slots still close.  Bloodstained sections of the east wall record a succession of violent incidents, the stains in layers of different age.  Old warden rotation logs are pinned above the entry: four-week shifts, three wardens per rotation, last entry more than a generation ago.
