@@gMountain Bear Scrublands@@N~
The vegetation changes abruptly here at the no_mob boundary where the scraggly shrubs and ground-hugging volcanic soil plants give way to the first genuine scrubland growth tolerated by the mountain bear populations.  Mountain bears are habitat-engineers — their seasonal foraging, scent-marking, and denning behavior structures the vegetation around their territories in ways that are readable to experienced observers.  The scrubland here is in good health, suggesting stable and active bear presence.  The ash content in the soil changes at this line too: above it, the substrate carries the heavy volcanic chemistry of extended residence in the bears' territory; below, it is the lighter ash-and-basalt mix of the foothill approaches.
