The three patrol circuits listed are: THRESHOLD ROAD (daily, two wardens), CANYON APPROACH (every third day, four wardens with a guide), and OUTER PERIMETER (weekly, one senior warden).  The canyon approach patrol required a guide because the canyon approach routes were considered hazardous enough that solo navigation without local knowledge was not authorized.  No patrol guide assignments appear in this schedule — the guide position is listed as "to be designated."  It was never designated.
