ashrunner~
The ashrunner birds are small, dark-feathered avians that pick their way across the fan surface with a distinctive high-stepping gait designed to distribute their weight.  They cluster around gas seep areas where the surface crust is thinnest, feeding on the sulfur-tolerant insects that colonize the seep margins.  Where ashrunners congregate, sink crust risk is high — the birds know to step carefully, and their presence is the most reliable ground-quality indicator available in the fan country.
