@@rSeven Ash Arches — Second and Third Arches@@N~
The second and third arches stand as a pair, their geometric profiles similar enough to confirm a single rebuilding era even to an untrained eye — @@r the subtle difference in arch geometry@@N between the two reveals a different master builder on each: the second arch uses a slightly flatter profile consistent with institutional Ventspeaker construction standards, while the third arch uses a more pronounced curve that the commission associated with a later period when the Ventspeaker lineage was already fragmenting and individual builders were beginning to deviate from canonical forms.  The stone facing is the same material on both, quarried from the same source formation somewhere to the north, its pale grey providing strong contrast to the dark basalt of the First Arch behind.  At the base of the third arch's west pier, a carved inscription in a script the commission could not fully translate records what is believed to be a dedication or dedication date for this rebuilding generation.
