E
name-stone symbols~
The symbol vocabulary on the Cinderteeth name-stones uses a system of approximately forty distinct carved marks identified by the commission's epigraphic survey team.  Most marks appear to function as modifiers to the personal name-glyphs, recording the individual's vocation, their specific vent affiliation, and their status in the Ventspeaker hierarchy.  The connection to the Bellspine resonance anchor sites is structural: name-stone symbol sets appear at each anchor commissioning record the commission found in the Bellspine, suggesting that the name-stone vocabulary and the anchor-commissioning vocabulary share a common symbolic register, consistent with a unified institutional system covering both the resonance anchor program and the vent ritual network.
