surveyor team loss~
The commission's records contain a notation about the Conclave survey team that operated this cache during the final phase of Conclave activity in the Western Fold.  The team consisted of four surveyors and their instruments, tasked with completing a thermal gradient survey of the approach corridor.  The commission determined that the team's departure from this cache coincided with the onset of a major volcanic gas event in the Fold interior — gas concentration records in the commission's geological survey suggested the event would have been survivable with proper equipment, but the survey team's instruments were apparently set up in the interior when the event occurred rather than properly secured at the cache.  The commission's notation concludes: "instrumental loss confirmed — personnel fate undocumented — survey data unrecovered."
