@@rLast Ventspeaker's Oracle Ground@@N~
The oracle ground of the last Ventspeaker is the oldest undisturbed sacred site in the Western Fold approach — @@r the vent at its center@@N has been ringed with carved stones since before any other structure in this zone existed, its stones worn by generations of ritual use to a smoothness that ordinary weathering could not produce, each stone selected for a mineral composition that resonates differently under the vent's gas pressure.  Cairn-Mother Retha An, who was the last active Ventspeaker to hold this site before the Conclave's occupation, is present here in a form that is not fully material: a preserved ghost, bound to the oracle ground by the accumulated weight of the centuries she spent here, her form readable as an elderly woman in traditional Ventspeaker garb whose edges blur into the vent smoke.  She did not choose to remain — the binding is the site's own nature, the oracle ground having a quality that the commission's cultural record describes as "retentive": it holds things that have poured enough of themselves into it over sufficient time.  Retha An is aware of visitors and responds to them with the clarity of someone who has had a very long time to think; she is neither hostile nor welcoming, but her knowledge of the Ventspeaker tradition, the Fold's geological character, and the institutional history of the approach zone is comprehensive.  The commission's cultural survey team spent three visits here before she trusted them enough to provide substantive information, which is recorded in survey report volume seven as the most detailed primary source on Ventspeaker doctrine and practice in the commission's entire archive.
E
mountain-tongue born~
The Ventspeaker title "mountain-tongue born" was given to practitioners whose oracle capacity was judged to originate in direct geological sensitivity rather than trained technique — the mountain itself was considered to speak through them rather than to them.  Cairn-Mother is the highest Ventspeaker designation, held only by the practitioner judged to have the deepest geological bonding.  Retha An held the Cairn-Mother designation for over sixty years before the Conclave's arrival and continued holding it after the Conclave occupied the Fold, working in reduced circumstances from this oracle ground alone after the other practitioners were displaced.  The commission documented her as "the primary repository of intact Ventspeaker institutional knowledge in the Cinderteeth" — a status she retains in her ghostly continuation with all the institutional knowledge she accumulated intact.
