@@yWestern Fold Interior — Thermal Chimney Row@@N~
The thermal chimney row is a stretch of the approach interior where a series of small vertical vent channels emerge from the Fold floor in a roughly linear arrangement — @@y each chimney@@N is a narrow column of darker rock rising perhaps thirty centimeters above the surrounding surface, its top open and emitting a thin continuous thread of gas and warmth that is only visible in cool weather but perceptible by smell and thermal sensation year-round.  The chimneys are a natural feature, not constructed, but they have clearly been noted as significant by both the Ventspeaker tradition — name-stones are positioned at the base of three of the chimneys — and the commission, whose geological survey identified the chimney row as a surface expression of a sub-grade fracture network providing direct pathway to the geothermal source.  The approach route runs between the chimneys without difficulty; their spacing is generous enough that the passage through them does not require deviation.
