@@yIron-Rich Spring Basin@@N~
The iron-rich spring basin is the primary surface expression of the geothermal spring network feeding the Western Fold's mineral environment — @@y the basin itself@@N is a natural bowl in the Fold floor where spring water emerges from multiple fractures and collects before overflowing into the drainage channels that cross the central expanse.  The iron content of the water gives the basin a vivid rust-orange color that contrasts strikingly with the surrounding rock, and the iron-moss mineral accretion that forms on every rock surface within splash distance of the basin creates an orange-red biological-mineral composite that extends the basin's color palette outward.  The water is hot — not boiling, but hot enough that prolonged contact is unpleasant — and the steam rising from it in cooler weather creates a persistent haze at the basin level.  The Ventspeaker ritual use of this basin is documented in the commission's cultural survey as the most important water-based ritual site in the Fold approach zone.
E
ritual pool chemistry~
The Ventspeaker ritual use of the iron spring basin was centered on the specific mineral chemistry of its water: the iron, sulfur, and trace element composition was held to give the water properties that the Ventspeaker doctrine characterized as "mountain-knowing" — the ability to transmit geological information to a prepared practitioner through sustained contact.  The commission's cultural survey team documented the ritual pool practice in detail, noting that the chemical composition of the spring water includes trace mineral compounds from the geothermal source's deep rock chemistry that are not present in surface water anywhere else in the mountain range.  Whether those trace compounds have any physiological effect beyond the obvious thermal and chemical properties the commission could document is left open in their report — the commission's cultural survey team was careful to record Ventspeaker practices accurately without adjudicating their claimed efficacy.
~
