#6545
@@yTiered Fire-Pit Complex — Inner Sanctum@@N~
The inner sanctum is the inmost space of the tiered fire-pit complex, its walls the oldest masonry in the entire Fold and its floor the most archaeologically layered — @@y the stratigraphic record@@N here tells the full story of the Ventspeaker tradition's use of this site and its abrupt end: combustion layers begin deep in the deposit, regular and dense through the entire Ventspeaker period, and then stop with the same abruptness documented at the fire-pit sites in the approach zone.  The combustion end layer coincides precisely with the Conclave's first documented occupation of the Fold — the same date at which Conclave equipment began to appear in the archaeological record elsewhere in the site — making this the most direct material evidence of the displacement event.  The Ash Cult has not re-lit the inner sanctum's fire pit — whether from reverence, practical constraint, or doctrinal decision is unclear — making it the only space in the fire-pit complex where the original Ventspeaker archaeology is preserved without an overlay of current occupation.
E
ventspeaker use layer cessation~
The Ventspeaker combustion end layer at the inner sanctum is unique in the Western Fold archaeological record for its precision: unlike the gradual reduction in activity visible at some approach zone sites, the inner sanctum's combustion stops in a single layer with no evidence of reduced activity before cessation.  This suggests the Ventspeaker tradition's use of the inner sanctum was maintained at full intensity until the moment it ended — not a gradual withdrawal but an abrupt stop.  Commission archaeologists interpreted this pattern as consistent with a specific displacement event rather than a gradual institutional decline: the people who used this space stopped because they were made to stop, not because their tradition was failing.  The coincidence with the Conclave occupation date means the inner sanctum's combustion record is essentially a timestamp for the moment of institutional overwriting — the most precise dating available for the transition from Ventspeaker to Conclave control of the Western Fold.
~
