#6597
@@yGlasswalk Zone — Harvest Plateau@@N~
The harvest plateau is the primary extraction area for Ember Crown obsidian, its broad flat surface providing stable footing for the extraction equipment and sorting operations that constitute organized glasswalk harvest — @@y emergency retreat protocol signs@@N are still bolted to stakes along the plateau's edges, their instructions laminated against weather damage and their text remarkably specific: "TREMOR SEQUENCE THREE — EVACUATE NORTHWEST — DO NOT CARRY LOADS — MINIMUM THREE MINUTES TO SHELTER BEFORE SUSTAINED TREMOR ONSET."  The detailed protocol language confirms that extraction crews developed sophisticated tremor-response procedures based on experience with the Firsttooth's specific behavior, distinguishing between different tremor sequences with different safety implications.  The plateau's current state suggests recent extraction — fresh tool marks on several glass faces, a cleared sorting area, and an intact equipment cache suggest a crew was operating here within the past season.
E
licensed extraction rules~
The commission's survey of the glasswalk harvest zone documented the extraction licensing system administered from the Kiess ranger guild at the time of their survey.  Licenses were issued per-season, limited to specific extraction zones on the harvest plateau, and required deposit of safety bonds forfeited if extraction crews did not comply with emergency protocols.  The rules included: no night extraction; minimum four-person crews; mandatory tremor monitor posting during extraction sessions; mandatory evacuation of all personnel and equipment on any tremor sequence rated three or above; and prohibition of extraction within the inner caldera boundary.  The commission found the licensing system generally effective but noted that the bonds' forfeit value was insufficient to motivate compliance in crews operating at the margin of profitability.
