#6600
@@rVent-Gas Inversion Pocket Beta@@N~
The second vent-gas inversion pocket is larger than the first and has a recorded history of fatalities — @@r commission survey stakes around the pocket@@N carry both the standard detection protocol and a list of documented incidents: three extraction crew members in different seasons, a commission geological survey solo who was operating outside the mandatory partner protocol, and two individuals whose identities the commission could not determine from remains.  The pocket's larger size gives it slightly more approach margin than the first — the commission's measurement found approximately two meters of detectable-odor warning at still-air conditions — but its larger gas reservoir means that a single deeply breached entry has a worse outcome than at the smaller pocket.  The commission's cultural survey noted that the death cases at this pocket were the primary impetus for the formalization of the vent-gas detection protocol: the incidents turned informal knowledge into documented required procedure.
E
pocket beta death cases~
The three confirmed extraction crew deaths at Pocket Beta occurred in two separate incidents over the space of four seasons.  The first incident: a three-person crew in the process of retreating from a nearby extraction site, moving quickly in reduced visibility, entered the pocket before the lead person detected the odor; two members of the crew collapsed before the third could extract them, and the extraction attempt brought the third within the lethal concentration zone.  All three were recovered from the pocket rim by a rescue party working from windward.  The second incident: a lone extraction worker, violating the partner protocol, entered the pocket in an apparent attempt to shortcut across the depression; their remains were found at the pocket floor.  The commission's survey report describes the pocket beta fatalities as the direct cause of the licensing system's partner requirement and the detailed evacuation protocol signage installed throughout the glasswalk zone.
~
