The Widow's Spire base is where the Spire's ancient basalt meets the Crown's accumulated debris — @@r the base rock@@N is visibly different from everything around it: darker, more uniform in color, harder to the tap of a boot, lacking the thermal fracture patterns that mark Crown surface rock elsewhere.  The geological assessment the commission conducted at the base identified the Spire as a remnant of the Crown's pre-volcanic foundation — old enough to predate the Firsttooth's volcanic history, its composition inconsistent with any of the identified eruptive chemistry, suggesting it was already here when the volcano formed around it.  The base provides a genuine rest point before the exposed climb above: sheltered from the prevailing wind on the Spire's lee side and warm from the thermal mass of the dense basalt, it is one of the few positions in the upper Crown that can be occupied for extended periods without thermal discomfort.
