The Secondtooth summit ridge extension continues the summit terrain east of the caldera watcher's established territory — @@r the extension terrain@@N shows the same thermal character as the watcher's ground but at a reduced intensity that reflects the extension's position outside the core territory, the dominant caldera watcher's presence affecting this area through the indirect effects of territorial marking and creature-movement suppression rather than direct occupation.  Commission survey records describe the summit ridge extension as the route used for the Secondtooth caldera's eastern-face survey, the ridge providing access to caldera features not visible from the western approach.  The caldera watcher's ground connects west and the far summit ridge extends east.
