The far eastern end of the Secondtooth summit ridge is the most distant accessible point in the caldera's summit zone — @@r the far ridge@@N position provides the best available view of the caldera's eastern face, a geological feature that the commission's survey team documented as showing the most recent significant structural modification in the range: a collapse event that the team estimated had occurred within the last several decades based on the freshness of the exposed rock faces.  The summit ridge extension connects west.
