@@rSecondtooth Summit — Northern Viewpoint@@N~
The northern viewpoint above the Secondtooth summit ridge extension faces the terrain north of the coupled caldera system — @@r the northern view@@N from summit altitude on the Secondtooth takes in the full extent of the terrain separating the Cinderteeth from the Great Northern Forest: the upper Crown terrain, the approach zones, and in favorable visibility conditions the distant forest canopy itself on the horizon.  Commission survey records note the northern viewpoint as the position from which the GNF survey team's complementary observations were made, the two teams conducting simultaneous observations from their respective terrain positions to document the transition zone between the volcanic mountain and the forest territory.  The summit ridge extension connects south and the northern summit terrace extends east.
