#6709
@@rSecondtooth Northern Summit Terrace@@N~
The northern summit terrace of the Secondtooth is an exposed platform at near-summit altitude — @@r the terrace's position@@N on the caldera's northern exterior face receives both the thermal output from the caldera above and the cold northern wind that descends from higher elevations, a combination that the commission's meteorological notes describe as producing the range's most variable local weather conditions: sudden thermal inversions, unexpected wind-direction reversals, and the distinctive "summit breath" phenomenon where the thermal updraft from the caldera briefly overwhelms the prevailing wind pattern.  Commission survey records document the northern terrace as the position used for meteorological monitoring during the Ember Crown survey phase.  The northern viewpoint connects west and the far northern approach extends to the north.
