@@rUpper Approach — Eastern Scree Corridor@@N~
The eastern scree corridor branches off the upper caldera approach, offering an alternative traverse along the caldera's eastern face exterior — @@r the corridor terrain@@N is looser than the main approach, its surface composed of smaller scoria fragments that shift under foot load in a way that the more consolidated main approach surface does not, requiring careful movement but providing access to caldera exterior features on the eastern face.  Commission survey records describe the eastern corridor as the route used for eastern-face feature access during the upper caldera survey phase.  The main upper caldera approach connects west and the corridor extends east and north.
